'''Antonio de la R<U+00FA>a'''<ref>{{cite web | title = Antonio de la R<U+00FA>a | publisher = ''Televisa Espectaculos'' | year = 2009 | url = http://www2.esmas.com/entretenimiento/biografias/009418/antonio-rua | accessdate = 2009-06-17}}</ref> (born [[February 26]], [[1973]]<!-- reference from spanish wikipedia (http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antonio_de_la_R%C3%BAa) -->, in [[C<U+00F3>rdoba, Argentina|C<U+00F3>rdoba]], [[Argentina]]), is the oldest son of the Argentine ex-president, [[Fernando de la R<U+00FA>a]] (who governed Argentina  from 1999 to 2001) and [[In<U+00E9>s Pertin<U+00E9>]]. He was an advisor to his father during his father's presidency and one of the heads of his father<U+2019>s presidential campaign. 

Though he held no formal position in his father's government, he was the chief architect of his father's election campaign; his success led his father to continue to turn to him for political advice after his ascension to the presidency.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.3puntos.com/seccion.php3?numero=264&nEsp=185&seccion=tapa|title=Yo me borro: Antonio de la R<U+00FA>a decidi<U+00F3> alejarse de la pol<U+00ED>tica|publisher=3 Puntos|accessdate=2007-07-09}}</ref> He was pointed to as the leader of the "Sushi set", a group of young officials so-called due to their alleged preference for expensive Japanese cuisine; they were sometimes criticised for their influence on politics.<ref>{{cite news|publisher=The New Statesman|last=Wilson|first=Bee|date=2002-01-14|accessdate=2007-07-09|title=Meat Wars|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/200201140039}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ayudatareas.com.ar/noticias2/39/archivo-ac2454.shtml|title=El grupo sushi, a punto de abandonar la escena pol<U+00ED>tica|publisher=La Naci<U+00F3>n|last=Litre|first=Gabriela|accessdate=2007-07-09}}</ref> After the collapse of the de la R<U+00FA>a presidency, Antonio focused his energies on philanthropy and distanced himself from politics, thus marking the end of the influence of the "Sushi Group".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.revista-noticias.com.ar/ed_1564/articulo.php?art=52|last=Seiffert|first=Daniel|publisher=Revista Noticias|title=Sushi filantr<U+00F3>pico|language=Spanish|accessdate=2007-07-09}}</ref>


Antonio, who is a [[lawyer]] and a [[bachelor]], has been [[paparazzi]] fodder since his father arrived at the La [[Casa Rosada]] (the Pink House), as the presidential seat in Argentina is called.  In 2000, he started dating singer [[Shakira]], in a romance that made headline news all over [[Latin America]]. He and Shakira have been seen together at many important events, including visiting with [[Dominican Republic]] president [[Hip<U+00F3>lito Mej<U+00ED>a]]. In March 2001, he proposed to her, with future plans to marry.<ref> VOY Music. [http://www.voymusic.com/radio/news-50610-shakira_prepares_wedding "Shakira Prepares Wedding" [[December 29]] 2006]</ref>Antonio de la Rua had a key role in negotiating Shakira<U+2019>s contract with Live Nation placing her among the most select group of artists including Madonna, U2 and Jay-Z. The contract signed with the largest event producer in the world for 10 years is worth between 70 and 100 million dollars<ref>http://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/07/03/shakira-leaves-epic-signs-massive-live-nation-deal/ Rolling Stone's article</ref>.


In December 2006 Antonio de la Rua together with a group of prominent Latin American businessmen and artists founded [[ALAS_Foundation]]<ref>http://www.nytimes.com/2009/06/07/magazine/07Shakira-t.html?scp=1&sq=shakira&st=cse Shakira's Children, article by the New York Times</ref>. Foundation ALAS is a non-for profit organization that promotes Early Childhood Development in Latin America<ref>http://www.alasthemovement.org/pages/about/about_aboutalas_en.asp About Alas</ref>.

<ref>http://www.alasthemovement.org/pages/about/about_leadership_en.asp ALAS' leadearship</ref>Foundation ALAS has [[Nobel Prize]] winner [[Gabriel Garcia Marquez]] as its Honorary President, as founding members Carlos Slim, Alejandro Santo Domingo, Antonio de la Rua, Alejandro Soberon, Alejandor Bulgheroni among others and artists Shakira, Fher Olivera, Alejandro Sanz, Juan Luis Guerra and Diego Torres among others<ref>http://www.alasthemovement.org/pages/about/about_activists_en.asp ALAS' activists</ref>.<br />

Antonio de la Rua owns and develops a 700 acre bahamian island called <ref>http://www.privateislandsonline.com/bondscbbh.htm Private Islands Online</ref>Bonds Cay. The island has Pink Floyd's [[Roger_Waters|Roger Waters]], [[Shakira]] and spanish singer-songwriter [[Alejandro_Sanz|Alejandro Sanz]] among its future residents<ref>http://www.forbes.com/2006/10/24/shakira-waters-bronfman-life-re-cx_lm_1025movers.html Forbes article</ref>.<br><br><br>

